<!-- PROBLEM -->
<div class="cs-body-section">
  <div class="cs-section-header">
    <div class="cs-section-num">01 — Problem</div>
    <h2 class="cs-section-title">three gaps, one lever</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="cs-content">
    <div></div>
    <div class="cs-content-body">
      <p>Despite existing education and visibility work, we were seeing three persistent gaps in the marketplace.</p>
      <p><strong>Owners struggled to identify reliable sitters in search.</strong> There was no clear signal distinguishing high-trust supply from the rest.</p>
      <p><strong>Sitters saw metrics but felt no strong, ongoing motivation to change behaviour.</strong> Sitter Insights told them how they were doing — it didn't tell them what it was worth.</p>
      <p><strong>Diversion remained a large, strategic revenue leak</strong> despite education and policy work. Sitters could understand what Rover expected and still leave with their repeat clients.</p>
      <p>Internally, we framed this as needing a third lever — a status program that could: gamify the behaviours we cared about; direct demand to our most reliable supply; and start reducing off-platform bookings by tying status to on-platform repeat behaviour and diversion-related disqualifiers.</p>
    </div>
